---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About Maxi Cespedes"
  description="About Maxi, a frontend engineer writing about React, performance, architecture, testing, SEO, and AI-era product work."
>
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    I’m Maxi Cespedes 🇦🇷,, a frontend engineer based in the Netherlands🇳🇱. This site is where I publish opinionated writing about frontend engineering, product taste, performance, AI-assisted workflows, and the parts of software work that sit between code and judgment.
  </p>
  <div class="image-wrapper">
    <img src="/images/posts/maxi-2025.jpg" alt="Maxi" class="about-img" width="400" height="400" loading="eager" decoding="async" />
  </div>

  <h2>What is this blog about?</h2>
  <p>
    I started my career as a fullstack engineer but quickly gravitated toward frontend engineering, because I care deeply about how interfaces feel, how fast they behave, and how product decisions show up in the browser. Over the years I have spent a lot of time thinking about what makes digital products useful, legible, and commercially viable.
  </p>
  <p>
    The writing here sits at the intersection of React, UI performance, frontend architecture, testing, SEO, and the more political side of engineering work: priorities, tradeoffs, and the way product reality bends technical ideals.
  </p>
  <p>
    I am also a founder of many failed projects. That matters because it changed how I think about frontend work. I care less about framework tribalism and more about whether a product is understandable, reliable, and worth using.
  </p>
  <p>
    Lately the blog also follows my transition through the AI era: what changes when agents can write code, what still requires experience, and where frontend engineers should widen their scope without losing rigor.
  </p>

  <h2>Who this is for</h2>
  <p>
    If you are a frontend engineer who cares about product quality, performance, architecture, testing, and the future of the role, you are in the right place.
  </p>

  <h2>Want to talk?</h2>
  <p>I have a 100% reply ratio if you want to know more.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/neomaxzero/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://www.github.com/neomaxzero/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
    <li><a href="mailto:maxicespedes7@hotmail.com">maxicespedes7@hotmail.com</a></li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>

